---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Jacob Weinbren" description="An introduction to Jacob">
	<h1 class="text-5xl">Jacob Weinbren</h1>
	<h2 class="text-2xl mt-4">
		I'm a programmer, blogger, and data visualiser.
	</h2>
	<div class="max-w-3xl">
		<h3 class="text-lg mt-4">
			You can check out my <a href="/projects" class="font-semibold"
				>projects</a
			>. Or you can give my <a href="/blog" class="font-semibold">blog</a>
			a read.
		</h3>
		<p class="mt-4">
			I'm experienced in web development with a deep understanding of the
			full web development stack, including Git, PHP, HTML, CSS,
			JavaScript, React, Svelte, Next.JS, and WordPress. I'm a bit
			advocate for open source, and you can find all my code on <a
				href="https://github.com/JacobWeinbren/"
				class="font-semibold">Github</a
			>.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-2">
			Skilled in backend technologies such as Python and Java, with a
			preference for agile methodologies and a strong grasp on data and
			server management tools such as Docker, AWS, MySQL, and Google
			Analytics.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-2">
			My work in data visualisation focuses on mapping and real-time
			charting, complementing my technical expertise with a strong
			foundation in cultural and literary analysis.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-2">
			I have proven teamwork and execution skills, honed through
			large-scale projects at previous employers.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-2">
			Feel free to reach out and <a
				href="mailto:jacobweinbren@gmail.com"
				class="font-semibold">contact me</a
			>.
		</p>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
